GEMINI-CURSES(1)           User Commands           GEMINI-CURSES(1)

NAME
    gemini-curses - ncurses terminal interface for the Gemini API

SYNOPSIS
    gemini-curses
    gemini-curses <session_name>
    gemini-curses --resume <session_name>
    gemini-curses --list
    gemini-curses --version
    gemini-curses --help

DESCRIPTION
    gemini-curses is a Python ncurses interface for Gemini. It is the
    full-screen terminal interface companion to the Bash gemini-cli tool.

    It provides:
        - scrollable transcript area
        - multiline input box
        - proper cursor movement
        - named and resumable sessions
        - timestamped logs
        - rolling memory context
        - attachment extraction for code blocks

SESSION MANAGEMENT
    gemini-curses
        Start a new timestamped session.

    gemini-curses <name>
        Start or open a named session.

    gemini-curses --resume <name>
        Resume an existing named session. If the session does not exist,
        the command exits with an error.

    gemini-curses --list
        List saved sessions.

    gemini-curses --version
        Display version information.

    gemini-curses --help
        Display built-in help.

CONTROLS
    Enter
        Insert newline in the input box.

    Ctrl+G
    F5
        Send the current message.

    F10
    Ctrl+Q
        Quit the interface.

    PgUp
        Scroll transcript upward.

    PgDn
        Scroll transcript downward.

    Arrow keys
        Move cursor inside the input box.

    Home
    End
        Move cursor to beginning or end of current input line.

    Ctrl+U
        Clear current input.

    Ctrl+L
        Redraw screen.

    Tab
        Insert four spaces.

CONFIGURATION
    Configuration file:
        ~/.config/gemini-cli/config

    The ncurses version intentionally uses the same configuration file as
    the Bash version.

    Supported keys:

        MODEL
            Gemini model identifier.
            Default: gemini-2.5-flash

        HISTORY_LIMIT
            Number of recent conversation entries retained in memory.
            Default: 12

        GEMINI_API_KEY
            Optional API key. Environment variable takes priority.

        SESSION_DIR
            Directory used for session log storage.
            Default: ~/.gpt

        ATTACHMENT_DIR
            Directory used for extracted code artifacts.
            Default: SESSION_DIR/attachments

ENVIRONMENT
    GEMINI_API_KEY
        Preferred API key source.

        Precedence:
            1. Environment variable
            2. Config file

FILES
    ~/.config/gemini-cli/config
        Configuration file.

    SESSION_DIR/*.log
        Session log files.

    ATTACHMENT_DIR/
        Extracted code block attachments.

ATTACHMENT SYSTEM
    Markdown fenced code blocks returned by Gemini are extracted from
    terminal display and saved into ATTACHMENT_DIR.

    The original raw Gemini response remains preserved in the session log.

    File names follow this pattern:

        <session>-<type>-NN.<extension>

    Examples:

        android-backup-python-01.py
        linux-help-bash-02.sh
        notes-json-01.json

SESSION NAMES
    Session names are sanitized for filesystem safety.

    Characters outside letters, numbers, dot, dash, and underscore are
    converted to underscores.

MEMORY MODEL
    gemini-curses keeps a rolling conversation context in memory.

    When resuming an existing session, the tool rebuilds recent memory from
    the session log.

LIMITATIONS
    - Requires Python 3 with curses support
    - Requires internet access
    - API quota restrictions apply
    - Long input lines horizontally scroll inside the input area
    - No mouse support in this first release

VERSION
    gemini-curses version 0.1.0

